emius SDK, as used by hundreds of WordPress plugin and theme developers, was vulnerable to Cross-Site Request Forgery and Information disclosure due to missing capability checks and nonce protection on the _get_debug_log, _get_db_option, and the _set_db_option functions in versions up to, and including 2.4.2. Any WordPress plugin or theme running a version of Freemius less than 2.4.3 is vulnerable.","date":"2022-03-04"}],"impact":[]},{"uuid":"112723977d5ac53cf1d4612a818ce824ecaace26d23ecba8c9e50c8a575e6a9d","name":"Royal Addons for Elementor \u2013 Addons and Templates Kit for Elementor [royal-elementor-addons] < 1.3.56","description":null,"operator":{"min_version":null,"min_operator":null,"max_version":"1.3.56","max_operator":"lt","unfixed":"0","closed":"0"},"source":[{"id":"CVE-2022-4102","name":"CVE-2022-4102","link":"https:\/\/www.cve.org\/CVERecord?id=CVE-2022-4102","description":"[en] The Royal Elementor Addons WordPress plugin before 1.3.56 does not have authorization and CSRF checks when deleting a template and does not ensure that the post to be deleted is a template. This could allow any authenticated users, such as subscribers, to delete arbitrary posts assuming they know the related slug.","date":"2023-01-09"},{"id":"963a712124d77ce0e7252f81c26723107a25faa4","name":"WordPress  Royal Elementor Addons Plugin  < 1.3.56 is vulnerable to Arbitrary Content Deletion","link":"https:\/\/patchstack.com\/database\/wordpress\/plugin\/royal-elementor-addons\/vulnerability\/wordpress-royal-elementor-addons-plugin-1-3-56-subscriber-arbitrary-post-deletion-vulnerability","description":"Update the WordPress Royal Elementor Addons plugin to the latest available version (at least 1.3.56).\nKrzysztof Zaj\u0105c discovered and reported this Arbitrary Content Deletion vulnerability in WordPress Royal Elementor Addons Plugin. This could allow a malicious actor to delete content from your website such as pictures, posts or pages. This vulnerability has been fixed in version 1.3.56.","date":"2022-12-20"},{"id":"f54ff632616619bf5139b5063e7d9b8b300f0b63","name":"Royal Elementor Addons <=1.3.55 - Authenticated (Subscriber+) Arbitrary Post Deletion","link":"https:\/\/www.wordfence.com\/threat-intel\/vulnerabilities\/wordpress-plugins\/royal-elementor-addons\/royal-elementor-addons-1355-authenticated-subscriber-arbitrary-post-deletion","description":"The Royal Elementor Addons plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to authorization bypass due to a missing capability check during template deletion in the function wpr_create_template in versions up to, and including, 1.3.55. Furthermore, the plugin does not verify whether the deleted post is a template. This makes it possible for authenticated attackers, with subscriber-level permissions and above, to delete arbitrary posts and pages.","date":"2022-12-15"},{"id":"6365d4b78d05a9d1651fbdc3a350be1f29ec473b","name":"Royal Elementor Addons <= 1.3.55 - Cross-Site Request Forgery","link":"https:\/\/www.wordfence.com\/threat-intel\/vulnerabilities\/wordpress-plugins\/royal-elementor-addons\/royal-elementor-addons-1355-cross-site-request-forgery-2","description":"The Royal Elementor Addons plugin for WordPress is vulnerable to Cross-Site Request Forgery in versions up to, and including, 1.3.55. This is due to missing or incorrect nonce validation on the wpr_delete_template and wpr_create_template functions. This makes it possible for unauthenticated attackers to delete or create pages\/posts, via forged request granted they can trick a site administrator into performing an action such as clicking on a link.","date":"2022-12-15"},{"id":"c177f763-0bb5-4734-ba2e-7ba816578937","name":"Royal Elementor Addons &lt; 1.3.56 - Subscriber+ Arbitrary Post Deletion","link":"https:\/\/wpscan.com\/vulnerability\/c177f763-0bb5-4734-ba2e-7ba816578937","description":"The plugin does not have authorization and CSRF checks when deleting a template and does not ensure that the post to be deleted is a template. This could allow any authenticated users, such as subscribers, to delete arbitrary posts assuming they know the related slug.","date":null}],"impact":{"cvss":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:H\/PR:L\/UI:N\/S:U\/C:N\/I:L\/A:N","av":"n","ac":"h","pr":"l","ui":"n","s":"u","c":"n","i":"l","a":"n","score":"3.1","severity":"l","exploitable":"1.6","impact":"1.4"},"cvss3":{"version":"3.1","vector":"CVSS:3.1\/AV:N\/AC:H\/PR:L\/UI:N\/S:U\/C:N\/I:L\/A:N","score":"3.1","severity":"low","av":"network","ac":"high","pr":"low","ui":"none","s":"unchanged","c":"none","i":"low","a":"none","exploitable":"1.6","impact":"1.4"},"cwe":[{"cwe":"CWE-352","name":"Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF)","description":"The web application does not, or cannot, sufficiently verify whether a request was intentionally provided by the user who sent the request, which could have originated from an unauthorized actor."},{"cwe":"CWE-862","name":"Missing Authorization","description":"The product does not perform an authorization check when an actor attempts to access a resource or perform an action."}],"ssvc":{"exploitation":"poc","automatable":"no","technical_impact":"partial","kev":false,"kev_date":null}}},{"uuid":"bdf49bd10335ff1c578d8e0b5bd5cab2424b28f5414d15bd25abe47399de8cf5","name":"Royal Addons for Elementor \u2013 Addons and Templates Kit for Elementor [royal-elementor-addons] < 1.3.56","description":null,"operator":{"min_version":null,"min_operator":null,"max_version":"1.3.56","max_operator":"lt","unfixed":"0","closed":"0"},"source":[{"id":"CVE-2022-4103","name":"CVE-2022-4103","link":"https:\/\/www.cve.org\/CVERecord?id=CVE-2022-4103","description":"[en] The Royal Elementor Addons WordPress plugin before 1.3.56 does not have authorisation and CSRF checks when creating a template, and does not ensure that the post created is a template. This could allow any authenticated users, such as subscriber to create a post (as well as any post type) with an arbitrary title","date":"2023-01-09"},{"id":"3db6fc36f921